        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>508</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-003Q</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-003Q.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Almost Everywhere">Almost Everywhere</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors />
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>In measure theory, a property is said to hold "almost everywhere" (often abbreviated as <fr:link type="local" href="FA-003S.xml" addr="FA-003S" title="A.e.">a.e.</fr:link>) if the set of points where the property fails has <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0137">measure</fr:link> zero.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>If a property <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P(x)]]></fr:tex> holds for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  X \setminus  N]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-003C.xml" addr="FA-003C" title="Measurable Set">measurable set</fr:link> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ \mu (N) = 0]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P(x)]]></fr:tex> is said to hold almost everywhere on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>This concept is essential in <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0138">Lebesgue integration</fr:link> theory, as functions that differ only on a set of measure zero have the same Lebesgue integral.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>509</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-003P</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-003P.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Essential Upper Bound">Essential Upper Bound</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors />
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>An upper bound that holds <fr:link type="local" href="FA-003Q.xml" addr="FA-003Q" title="Almost Everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>For a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-003D.xml" addr="FA-003D" title="Measurable Function">measurable function</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> defined on a <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0135">measure space</fr:link>, a real number <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is an essential upper bound for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x) \leq  M]]></fr:tex> for <fr:link type="local" href="FA-003Q.xml" addr="FA-003Q" title="Almost Everywhere">almost every</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> in the domain.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
  </fr:backmatter>
